description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; – &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Administrative &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assistant &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Regional Capacity Management Team (RCMT).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an administrator for12 months (Secondment) to provide a comprehensive business administration support role together with being able to coordinate urgent care reports, support projects and maintain systems managed within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will provide business administrative, communicative, and promotional support to the RCMT by undertaking administrative duties associated with projects/service improvements as well support the business as usual.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will develop a sound knowledge of current systems and applications and liaise with RCMT Managers, Urgent Care Intelligence Centre, and end users to understand the use of the Escalation Management System (EMS), as well as support on new projects, initiatives and developments. With excellent all-round knowledge of IT in a Windows environment, we are looking for someone to become a subject matter expert in relation to the systems used in the Regional Capacity Management Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time 37.5 hours required, 5 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: Friday 6th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Administrative Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Natalie Butler&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: natalie.butler1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mobile: 07920 456 484&lt;/p&gt;
